The chairman, All Progressives Congress (APC) in Apa Local Government Area of Benue State, Mr Inalegwu Ichapi, is dead. Ichapi ‘s death was confirmed in a statement issued by the party’s Acting Publicity Secretary, Mr James Ornguga. Ornguga stated that the State Chairman of the party, Mr Abba Yaro, and his executive council were deeply saddened by the demise, adding that they sympathized with the family of the deceased and the entire Apa APC. “Until his death, Ichapi was APC chairman in Apa and has contributed immensely to the development and success of the party in the area. “Burial arrangement as released by his family indicates that wake in his honour will hold on March 11, 2020 at his family compound, Adija Village, Ugbokpo in Apa, while interment would hold on March 12,” NAN quoted him as saying. Ornguga prayed to God to give his family the fortitude to bear the painful loss.